sentences: Edgar Junius Hayes (May 23, 1902 – June 28, 1979) was an American jazz pianist and bandleader.
Born in Lexington, Kentucky, United States, Hayes attended Wilberforce University, where he graduated with a degree in music in the early 1920s.
In 1922, he toured with Fess Williams, and formed his own group, the Blue Grass Buddies, in Ohio in 1924.

From 1931 to 1936, Hayes played in and arranged for the Mills Blue Rhythm Band.
From 1937 to 1941, Hayes again led his own orchestra; Kenny Clarke was among his sidemen.
His most popular recording was a version of the song "Stardust" and the original recording of "In the Mood" which was later covered by Glenn Miller, both songs were recorded in 1938.
He moved to California in 1942, and led a quartet there for most of the decade.
